/* Press secretary Powell opinion article—UNDUE weight? */

Still [[WP:UNDUE]] (and unattributed) in the lede. The primary source opinion column by Carter's own press secretary simply cannot be used to support sweeping, unattributed, far-reaching factual claims in wikivoice like this, let alone in the lede. There is surely a reason that no prior version of the lede mentioned these alleged anecdotes in more than 15 years. Please stop edit warring and turning our encyclopedia into a political gossip tabloid.
/* Edit warring */ Re; the [[WP:ONUS]] is on you to obtain consensus for reinstating contentious material; please adhere to Wikipedia's core content policies and stop edit warring.
/* RFC on geography */ Re.

All editors are required to comply with Wikipedia's core content policies; no, you are not an exception. The editorial by Carter's press secretary is not reliable for factual statements per [[WP:RS]]: "Editorial commentary, analysis and opinion pieces [...] are reliable primary sources for statements attributed to that editor or author, but are rarely reliable for statements of fact." Powell's anecdote from an unnamed "friend" of George Will is gossip, not verified fact for an encyclopedia.
